post_text:
Record-Setting Performance! 🦅⛳️

The Argyle Eagles boys' golf team broke a two-day school record last weekend during the Lanny Wadkins Classic played at the Texas Rangers Golf Club. The Eagles shot 291 on Friday and 291 on Saturday for a 582 total.

Gaven Lane finished 2nd at 10-under par and also set the school record for a single round by shooting 65. He broke the record set by himself (66) at Robson Ranch in 2019 and Logan Diomede (66) at Tangle Ridge in 2018.

Nicholas Hance finished 5 under par and tied for 4th.

Team Final Scores
Gaven Lane 69-65
Nicholas Hance 69-70
Zane Griggs 76-80
Blake Kelly 77-79
Justus Christman 81-77

Great job Eagles!

#TogetherWeAreArgyle #EagleGolf

Bus Transportation Reminder

This is a friendly reminder for parents/guardians regarding district guidelines pertaining to students attempting to ride the bus home with friends.

For the safety of all our Eagle riders, bus transportation is provided only to registered bus riders. Students are only allowed to ride their assigned bus.

Emergency transportation may be granted on a temporary basis by the Assistant Director of Transportation. Also, please remember that notes from parents/guardians are not accepted as authorization to ride a bus.

If you have any questions or concerns, please contact the Argyle ISD Transportation Department at 940-464-7241 x6011 or click the link below to visit the Transportation webpage.

Bus Transportation website 🚍 ➡️ https://bit.ly/3k1RFcr

Due to flooding, a section of Old Justin Road is currently closed and this will impact bus routes this morning for students in the Harvest subdivision. Expect delays this morning for pickup due to this road closure.

Eagles, please exercise caution this morning as the rain continues in the area and watch for flooding on roadways.

The low area of Old Justin Road between Cleveland Gibbs Road and Prairie View Farms is shut down at this time.

WEATHER ALERT: TUESDAY, SEPT. 1

Argyle is experiencing thunderstorms and heavy rains this afternoon. Our campus staff and Argyle ISD Police Department will assist our Eagles students at release to help them safely reach their families in the pickup line and buses.

Eagle families, expect bus delays for afternoon dropoff as the heavy rains continue after 4 p.m.

Student drivers and families please be safe on the roads and watch for high waters.

UPDATE 3 PM: UPDATE 3 PM - Due to the severe weather, the Argyle High School campus is currently without internet.

#EagleSafe

Our virtual students impacted by the outage will not be counted absent. Our teachers will work with these students to help them with missed assignments once internet service is restored.

Eagle Football Ticket Update! 📢 🦅 🏈

Tomorrow morning, Eagle Stadium will be open from 6 a.m. to 8:30 a.m. to allow TICKETED fans the opportunity to save seats in the stands with stadium chairs for the varsity game vs. Decatur.

Stadium gates will be locked at 8:30 a.m.

Kickoff is 7:30 p.m. As previously communicated, Eagle Stadium will not have reserved seating.

Fans are ONLY allowed to save seats for the number of tickets they have purchased. This opportunity is being provided to ticketed fans to help curb the potential crowding when gates open at 5:45 p.m.

The game is SOLD out. As you enter the stadium, please have your digital tickets ready on your phone as you near the gates to help assist in making this an efficient process.

Go Eagles!

Road Construction Alert: Old Justin Road 🚧

Road construction will start Monday, Aug. 24 on Old Justin Road. Daily closures are scheduled and a detour will be available between Cleveland Gibbs Road and Prairie View Farms.

Traffic will be detoured to the shoulder daily from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Flagmen will be on-site assisting with traffic. The eastbound and westbound lanes will reopen at 4 p.m. each day.

Please use extra caution and avoid this route during construction hours. The road construction is expected to be completed in two weeks.

Bus Afternoon Arrival Times Update for Parents

Elementary buses are running about 15 minutes earlier than the current posted stop times in the afternoons. Please plan to meet your child's bus 15 minutes earlier than the posted time. This time adjustment has been due to the student loading process working much faster than anticipated.

We plan to have route times updated after the second week of school. Thank you very much for your patience and please remind your riders about wearing masks and using the provided hand sanitizer before boarding the buses.

It has been a thrill for our drivers to see our Eagle riders again!

post_text:
What a great first day in Argyle ISD! 🦅

The district welcomed back students for the start of the 2020-2021 school year on Monday, Aug. 17. Students returned to learning both in-person and virtually on all five campuses.

Monday marked the first time students were in classrooms since early March due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The return to learning was much different from the traditional setting with several safety guidelines and procedures in place to help protect students and teachers.

"It was such an exciting day for our district," Argyle ISD Superintendent Dr. Telena Wright said. "To see our Eagle students learning together again both in-person and virtually was unforgettable. Our teachers and staff did a tremendous job implementing the health protocols to help our Eagles feel safe from the moment they got on the bus or walked inside their campus. I am so grateful for the hard work of our teachers and administrators throughout this process that led to an incredible first day."

post_text:
Hello Eagle Families,

This is helpful information for Eagle students (in-person and virtual learners) who are attempting to access their Argyle ISD Google accounts.

LOGIN: Your assigned student email account (firstname.lastname@stu.argyleisd.com).

PASSWORD: Use "Aisd" followed by the student's ID number. For example - Aisd123456 (uppercase A and remaining letters are lowercase).

Student account passwords were reset to this default criteria on Friday.

Also, if you are signing in with your known login and password and are still not able to get access, please be sure you have filled out the Acceptable Use Policy as part of your online enrollment process. This step is required for your student to have access to their Argyle ISD Google account.

post_text:
Back-to-School 2020-2021: Virtual Convocation!

Argyle ISD hosted its annual Convocation for all employees earlier this week and this year's event was held virtually. This is traditionally a large gathering of all staff, but it was adjusted this year due to safety guidelines.

The campuses scheduled time to watch this year's Convocation presented on video. It included a message from Dr. Wright and district leadership with the theme of "Zooming Into the New Year." Dr. Wright was featured at Texas Motor Speedway, where the 2019-2020 school year ended with the Class of 2020 Graduation ceremony.

Argyle ISD student groups were featured in the video and the event included popcorn & candy served to staff to enjoy while watching the video.

Our teachers and staff are excited and ready to welcome our Eagles in-person and virtually on Monday morning!

post_text:
Today marked a special day in Argyle ISD. It was the return to the campuses and classrooms for our teachers as they reported for the 2020-2021 school year.

For many, it was the return to their beloved classrooms to work for the first time since early March. Their rooms were left behind as our schools closed for the remainder of the spring semester due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

Argyle ISD is blessed with so many amazing teachers and we are grateful for their commitment and passion for serving our Eagles.

We recognize that this year will be unlike any before and we stand together with our teachers to help and support them through so much uncertainty.

Because....#TogetherWeAreArgyle!

Back-to-School Reminder for Eagle Families

As we prepare for the 2020-2021 school year Argyle ISD campuses are currently in the process of adjusting student schedules for in-person and virtual instruction. This is due to meeting the safety guidelines for physical distancing and classroom capacity and meeting the needs of our virtual learners.

Parents, please note the schedules currently available in your student's Google Classroom may NOT reflect the final version of your child's class schedule for the upcoming year. Currently, campus administrators, teachers and counselors are making changes to these schedules to best address in-person and virtual instruction. Additional temporary changes to your child's schedule may appear before schedules are finalized.

Final schedules will be available soon.

Breaking News: UIL Releases Modified Schedule for 2020-2021

On Tuesday, the UIL released modifications to the 2020-2021 UIL calendar and updated COVID-19 risk mitigation guidelines, set to take effect August 1, 2020.

The athletic schedule will remain the same for Argyle High School and all Class 1A-4A schools.

➡️ Football & Volleyball practice start dates remain the same for AUG. 3.

➡️ Football first date for games remains the same AUG. 27 & AUG. 10 for Volleyball.

*5A-6A football/volleyball start dates postponed 5 weeks.

➡️ Band first day to begin contest show visual/marching curriculum - SEPT. 7; State championships DEC. 2020, date TBD

View the press release from the UIL
https://bit.ly/39ffdGG

Dr. Wright Joins Denton County Superintendents Requesting STAAR Suspension

Argyle ISD Superintendent Dr. Telena Wright has joined with other Denton County Superintendents and elected officials in requesting the state suspend STAAR testing for the 2020-2021 school year.

This formal request was sent to Governor Greg Abbott and Texas Education Agency Commissioner Mike Morath stating the need for the state to suspend STAAR along with the A-F grading system due to the current COVID-19 pandemic.

The letter states that by suspending the test and grading system it would allow schools to continue to maintain a safe and secure educational environment while allowing schools to provide quality education specific to each student's educational needs.

After schools began to close across the state in March due to COVID-19, Governor Abbott waived STAAR testing requirements for the 2019-2020 school year.

What a great partnership Argyle ISD has with CoServ!

CoServ recently presented a check amount of $20,441.34 to the district as a Capital Credit. As a valued member of the electric cooperative, Argyle ISD annually receives these retired funds from CoServ.

CoServ has been powering homes in Denton County for more than 80 years and is a proud Eagle Partner. 🦅💡🔌

Thank you CoServ, for helping support our Eagles!

AISD Superintendent, Dr. Telena Wright shares a special message with the AHS Seniors. She also announces the lighting of the AHS Eagle Stadium that will take place this Sunday at the Senior Parade. The lighting of Eagle Stadium symbolizes the light the class of 2020 has shined bright throughout the years at Argyle High School and during these challenging times. May your light continue to shine!
AISD High School
Videography: Greg Royar, Editing: AISD Communications Dept.
Music: BenSound.com

post_text:

We want to congratulate all of the Seniors and we hope they enjoy the special activities that are planned for them this weekend. We can't wait to celebrate their graduation on Monday evening at the Texas Motor Speedway. You did it Seniors!! You did it together!! #TogetherWeAreArgyle @AISD High School

post_text:
Daniel Rehmet, a 6th grade student at Argyle Middle School and his family joined the community of Argyle 3 years ago. Daniel's sweet spirit has made such an impact on so many of his classmates and teachers! In March, Daniel became ill. He had many tests run to determine what was going on within his body. On Friday, April 10, 2020, his family received the heartbreaking news that he has Leukemia. Daniel is in the hospital and has started his treatments. A gofundme page has been set up to contribute to his family in order to assist them with medical bills.

PLEASE CLICK HERE TO DONATE TO DANIEL REHMET"S GO FUND ME - https://www.gofundme.com/f/DanielRehmet?utm_medium=sms&utm_source=customer&utm_campaign=p_na+share-sheet&rcid=da1696dc4ff04f788af04da2eb485b3c
AISD Middle School

Dear Argyle ISD Community,

We are releasing a tentative summer camp schedule for 2020 with camps starting as early as June 1st. This schedule is for planning purposes only. We are continuing to work with state officials and the UIL to determine if and when we will actually be able to host camps. We will send out that information when it is available. We will also post the information on the athletics page of the AISD website.

2020 Argyle Education Foundation Gala Update:

Due to COVID-19, we will no longer hold our Gala on April 25, 2020. Now more than ever we recognize the need to support our teachers and classrooms. We remain committed to our support of Argyle Independent School District (AISD). Historically, the Gala has enabled us to raise funds that pay Science Technology Engineering and Math (STEM) teacher annual salaries and provide classroom grants to each school in the District.

In lieu of the Gala, please visit us at SupportArgyleISD.org and join our Direct Donation Campaign, where you may contribute. We hope you will connect with us on Facebook to stay up to date with this direct donation effort as well as forthcoming fundraisers.

Thank you for your understanding and support,
The Argyle Education Foundation Board of Directors
www.SupportArgyleISD.org
AISD Argyle West Elementary AISD Hilltop Elementary School AISD Intermediate School AISD Middle School AISD High School

Argyle ISD Technology is now providing live support (Distance Learning Technology Support) for guardians, students, and staff.

You can use our live chat 8am to 4pm, Monday through Friday on aisdit.com or call 940-202-9067 to leave a message for our Technology Helpdesk.

Our technicians work hard to provide the best service possible for our Argyle community. Unfortunately, due to the limitations of remote support, we cannot guarantee total resolution to all distance learning technology issues.

Some of the topics that are appropriate for live chat include, but are not limited to:
Chromebook issues
User account issues
Lost/Forgotten passwords
Issues with distance learning software used by the district

We cannot address the following issues in live chat:
Chromebook damages requiring physical repairs
Personal technology issues or consultation
AISD Argyle West Elementary AISD Hilltop Elementary School AISD Intermediate School AISD Middle School AISD High School

ARGYLE EDUCATION FOUNDATION GALA - TABLE SPONSORSHIPS

The Argyle Education Foundation is a volunteer organization dedicated to supporting STEM education in Argyle ISD. Last year we donated $168,000 for STEM teachers and programs, including $3,600 campus grants for each school.

Our District is growing and so are our goals. Our largest fundraiser of the year will be held at Robson Ranch on April 25. We invite you to join us for a fun-filled evening to support Argyle ISD! Table and sponsorship sales are now open. Please visit us at supportargyleisd.org for more information. We hope to see you there!
Argyle Education Foundation

post_text:
Congratulations to Mrs. Gloria Hocking, AISD PEIMS Coordinator and Qmlativ Liason. Mrs. Hocking was selected as a Skyward 2020 Leader in Excellence Award winner. Skyward received a number of outstanding nominations from district peers and Skyward staff. Mrs. Hocking's nomination stood out because of the success she experienced while using Skyward to move and inspire people with new ideas and initiatives.

Mrs. Hocking will be honored during the 2020 iCon opening remarks in February.

As a Leader in Excellence Award winner, Mrs. Hocking and Argyle ISD are a shining example of success in education and Skyward will share the story on a local and national level to secure recognition for her achievements. Award recipients will be promoted throughout the year by Skyward through various communication efforts such as news announcements, case studies, and media interviews.

Congratulations Mrs. Hocking!
AISD High School AISD Middle School AISD Intermediate School AISD Hilltop Elementary School AISD Argyle West Elementary

The AHS Theatre Department recently attended the Thespians State Festival in Grapevine. In all, 32 students attended and almost all competed in various events or auditioned for colleges. We had some fantastic results! All four of our performance pieces qualified for Nationals, which will be held this summer in Indiana.

Group Acting: Brooke Adamson, Connor McCue, Grace May, Levi Pabst, Mikayla Simmons, Jenna Schnabel and Noah Weeks. Group Musical: Bryn Jacobs, Kyndall Hennigan, Hannah Oldham, Grant Wright and Kennedy Webster. Solo Musical: Savannah DeShazo. Duet Musical: Jackson Barnes & Bella Zindel

College Auditions: Gracie Johnson, Milan McKenna, Colby Raasch and Avery Winter. Each student received over a dozen callbacks and/or immediate offers from multiple universities. Colby Raasch was also the recipient of a $1000 scholarship.

Jackson Barnes was selected as a Student Thespian Officer and will be assisting in running multiple events for student leadership and representing Argyle across the state.
AISD High School #ArgyleTheatreDepartment2019

post_text: Sixteen Argyle High School Choir students participated in the TMEA Region 2 All-State Pre-Area auditions. Out of the sixteen students who auditioned, ten of them are moving on to the final round of Area Auditions in January at TWU! This is the most students Argyle ISD has ever had advance to this round. The AHS Choir also has more students than any other school in their Region moving on to the Area round for the Small School All State process. Congratulations! AISD High School

post_text:
Remedy A Cappella participated in their first and only competition of the 2019-2020 school year and went up against 9 of the best HS A Cappella groups in the state of Texas! Four of the groups we were competing against have all competed in HS A Cappella National Finals in New York City multiple times over the past 10 years so the competition was extremely competitive! The hard work of the students truly paid off and they finished in 2nd Place at the SING Texas Vocal Arts Convention! This is Remedy's first time to place in the top 3 in a competitive a cappella event. Check out their award winning performance - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rHm1bovamXA
- or follow them on Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/remedyacappellatx/ - and on Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/remedy_acappella/!
AISD High School Remedy A Cappella

post_text:
This weekend, The Talon News competed in the state journalism competitions for writing, broadcast, and photography. Competition was against all schools in Texas with no divisional separations.

This year www.TheTalonNews.com placed 2nd overall Best of Show in online digital news program, placing second to McKinney high school’s first place. This is a huge accomplishment, as it is a reflection of our entire online news program.

Additionally, individual award winners placed in the following categories:
News Writing (Superior) - Jaclyn Harris
Feature Writing (Superior) - Ashlynn Roberts
Video Sports Story (Superior) - Campbell Wilmot
Cell Phone Photography (Excellent) - Josh Fritz
Sports Feature Writing (Superior) - Max Van Drunen

Additional Best of Show Staff:
Andrew Fritz, Alex Daggett, Sloan Dial, Rylie Halk and Delaney Lechowit

Information provided by: Mrs. Stacy Short
AISD High School

post_text:
The Cross Country Teams competed in the 4A-8 District Championship this morning placing 2nd in both Team divisions. Top 10 individual finishers on Varsity included: Claire Dalling (10th), Avery Junk (8th), Amaris McCasland (4th) and Lanie Rodgers (2nd). The Varsity Team will advance on to Regionals in Lubbock taking place on October 28th vying for a top finish against Decatur (District Champions). Top 10 individual finishers on JV included: Sloan Dial (10th) and Abby Baker (5th). Congratulations to all!
Photos by: Coach Martin
AISD High School Argyle Eagles Booster Club

shared_text:
Remedy A Cappella
October 11, 2019 at 5:02 PM ·

It’s official! Remedy A Cappella has been selected to perform and compete at the @singtexas Vocal Arts Convention! We are so excited to be performing alongside some of our best friends in the state. It’s going to be an exciting weekend of A Cappella music so head on over to singtexas.org to get your tickets for the Friday Night Scholastic competition and the Saturday Night Spectacular featuring HIVE, the UNT Green Tone, and Booker T’s Jazz Group V.I.N.Y.L! Thank you for everyone’s continued support!

TODAY IS THE LAST DAY TO ORDER YOUR THINK PINK T-SHIRT! Argyle ISD students and community members are invited to THINK PINK on October 25 as we have a district-wide PINK OUT to support Breast Cancer Awareness. Feel Good Tees has partnered with Pals at AHS to design this year's t-shirt. T-shirts are $20 and can be ordered now through Friday, October 11. Proceeds from this tee will benefit the National Breast Cancer Foundation.
